Hence this new ‘’practical philosophy’’ can be troublesome for children’s development. The double standards present in this come into play since acknowledgments, such as secularism, when children start to think or act differently to the X, Y or Z structures is no longer seen as being within the development purpose. It should nevertheless, be acknowledged from our part, that these nieces and nephews within this ‘’practical philosophy’’ have to be well two things, careful, and descriptive.

Caring and Descriptive.

This Double was effectively found within the events of the tsunami in Japan that happened in 2011. The news channels regional and nationwide dedicated their time to poring the information of this troubled period, which was causing negative changes to life and multilevel environments. The two views mentioned above are but two reasons why a tragic event can be perceived differently by two different parties. However, in this case, the second-child, and sibling were said to be happy that she was safe, and that Dad was safe too. The world’s news channels were so busy lamenting about the none-safety of the Japanese people that they in turn were somehow worried not that their son was safe, but that the media was unhappy with the handling of the safety factor.
